---
import { Code } from 'astro/components'
import Layout from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const CODE = `# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/BiteCodeLabs/guardian
# Navigate to the directory
cd guardian
# Install dependencies
npm install
# Build the bot
npm run build
# Start the bot
npm run start`

---

<Layout title="Guardian">
	<main>
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto dark:text-white md:py-32 md:flex">
      <div class="p-8 md:w-1/2">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-bold my-4">Guardian</h1>
        <p class="text-2xl my-8">
          Minecraft <b class="text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">Server Management</b> made easy with Guardian.
        </p>
        <a href="/docs/get-started/introduction" class="inline-block bg-green-700 hover:bg-green-800 text-white text-lg font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded">
          GET STARTED
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="w-full p-8 md:w-1/2 [&_pre]:p-4 [&_pre]:rounded-2xl [&_pre]:shadow-xl [&_pre]:border-2 [&_pre]:border-green-500">
        <Code code={CODE} lang="sh"/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-700 dark:bg-zinc-800">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto md:py-16 p-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-white text-6xl font-bold mb-16">Highlighted Features!</h1>
        <div class="md:flex md:justify-center space-y-8 md:space-y-0 md:gap-x-8 dark:text-white">
          <div>
            <div class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-zinc-900 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Applications</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 my-4">
                Guardian's Application feature sends users predetermined application questions, 
                compiles their responses, 
                and sends them to the admins for review.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-zinc-900 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Interviews</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 my-4">
                Accepted members get an interview thread, 
                allowing admins to ask questions and 
                interact with them further.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-zinc-900 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Whitelist Management</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 my-4">
                The Whitelist Manager features an auto-whitelist, 
                cross-platform event reflection for ban, kick, 
                and leave events, and the ability to remove inactive players.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto dark:text-white md:py-32 md:flex md:flex-wrap">
      <div class="p-8 md:w-1/2">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">Reliable</h2>
        <p class="text-lg my-8">
          Before its release, Guardian underwent rigorous testing to ensure its reliability.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-8 md:w-1/2">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">Easy To Setup</h2>
        <p class="text-lg my-8">
          Guardian is easy to set up and start using, whether you're hosting it on a Pterodactyl Panel 
          or self-hosting it on your own hardware.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-8 md:w-1/2">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">Open Source</h2>
        <p class="text-lg my-8">
          Guardian's source code is built on top of open-source software licensed under the MIT license, 
          which allows anyone to contribute, report bugs, and suggest improvements or features.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-8 md:w-1/2">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">User Friendly</h2>
        <p class="text-lg my-8">
          The creator of Guardian built it with the users in mind, especially as they were the primary user, 
          ensuring that server admins could use it more easily within their servers.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a href="/docs/get-started/introduction" class="w-fit px-8 my-4 text-center mx-auto block bg-green-700 hover:bg-green-800 text-white text-lg font-bold py-2 rounded">
        GET STARTED
      </a>
    </div>
	</main>
</Layout>
